"P3549881923" "Pizza Sauce Stained Sticky Note"
// LocationString :
// ProfessionString :
// AskAboutTextOverride :
// ContactRequiresText :
// IDontKnowYouString :
// NoTasksRemainingString :
// PlayerBusyString :
// ComeBackLaterString :
// FailsafeLevelString :

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page VigilanteToVillain Text :
"P3982997172" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Pizza Sauce Stained Sticky Note</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You found this sticky note stained with pizza sauce on a Family Capo who was enjoying a fine evening dinner at a local spaghetti hole with his wife and two kids. The problem was you knew he was a cop killer, so you stained the floor with his own pizza sauce and found this note tucked in his pocket.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>The note reads: Al, moved first meeting 1 hour later. Still at warehouse 12. Call Calloway and let the jarhead know.</scale></font></color><br><br>Calloway... that name is familiar... jarhead...? Could they mean Lieutenant Calloway of the Sky Raiders? What would the Family be doing having a meeting with them? One thing seems clear, they haven't met him yet. Hmmm... if the meeting is an hour later than originally planned you might be able to get the drop on Calloway before the Family knows he's there. Then you could masquerade as Calloway, get in close, and eliminate the boss of this operation. The resulting fallout between the groups could very well spark a war between them!"
// Answer Text :
"P3868969792" "VILLAIN: Masquerade as Calloway and spark a war"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


